Below is a ready-to-copy Google Gemini prompt you should use after uploading the CSV.

This prompt is written so that Gemini:

understands this is for Slack / management update

aggregates the data cleanly

produces counts + segregation

formats output in a presentable, copy-paste-friendly way



---

‚úÖ Google Gemini Prompt (Use This Exactly)

> I am uploading a CSV file that contains PSC-related data.

Please analyze the CSV and present the data in a clean, management-ready summary format suitable for posting directly in Slack.

Requirements:

1. First, provide a high-level summary with the following metrics:

Total PSCs

Completed PSCs

In-Progress PSCs

Pending / Not Started PSCs (if applicable)



2. Next, for the 52 PSCs, provide a segregation by geography, clearly grouped as:

Area

Market

Sub-Market



3. For each Area ‚Üí Market ‚Üí Sub-Market combination, provide:

Number of PSCs

Breakdown by status (Completed / In-Progress / Pending)



4. Present the output in two sections:

Section 1: Executive summary (bullet points or compact table)

Section 2: Area / Market / Sub-Market breakdown in a structured table



5. Ensure:

No raw data dumps

Clear labels and counts

Clean formatting that can be pasted directly into Slack or PPT




If any required fields (Area / Market / Sub-Market / Status) are missing or inconsistent in the CSV, clearly call that out and proceed with the available data.




---

‚úÖ What Gemini Will Give You (Expected Output)

Section 1 ‚Äì Summary (Slack Ready)

PSC Summary:
‚Ä¢ Total PSCs: 52
‚Ä¢ Completed: XX
‚Ä¢ In Progress: XX
‚Ä¢ Pending: XX

Section 2 ‚Äì Area / Market / Sub-Market Breakdown

Area: South
  Market: TN
    Sub-Market: Chennai
      - Total PSCs: 12 (Completed: 8 | In Progress: 4)

  Market: AP
    Sub-Market: Vizag
      - Total PSCs: 6 (Completed: 3 | In Progress: 3)

‚úÖ Easy to paste
‚úÖ Easy for leadership to read
‚úÖ No Excel needed


---

‚úÖ Optional Add-On (If You Want Even Cleaner Output)

Add this line at the end of the prompt if you want Slack emojis & emphasis:

> Highlight key numbers using bold formatting and keep the content concise for executive consumption.




